<h1 style="margin-bottom:0px;">Before you begin</h1><div class="f14 metric" style="color:#656668;display:flex;"><img src="/assets/images/calendar.png" style="height:12px;margin-top:auto;margin-bottom:auto;"><span class="updateDate">&nbsp; Updated on 26/06/2019</span> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; | &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <img src="/assets/images/updated.png" style="height:12px;margin-top:auto;margin-bottom:auto;"><span class="readTime">&nbsp; 2 minutes to read</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</div><br><div class="mw-parser-output"><p><br>
</p><p>Installing Operations Bridge on AWS is a process that includes many procedures and involves different personas. This section gives you an overview of the basic procedures in an Operations Bridge installation and the personas involved in the process. There is also a referenced architecture that will help you to get an overall view of the deployment process.
</p><p><a onclick="javascript:loadingImage(this);" class="image"><img alt="hcm 201811 aws install with efs vertica cluster.png" src="/mediawiki/images/1/10/hcm_201811_aws_install_with_efs_vertica_cluster.png" width="802" height="760" data-file-width="802" data-file-height="760"></a>
</p>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Personas">Personas</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=Operations_Bridge:2019.05/BYBOpsB&amp;veaction=edit&amp;section=1" class="mw-editsection-visualeditor" title="Edit section: Personas">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-divider"> | </span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=Operations_Bridge:2019.05/BYBOpsB&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1" title="Edit section: Personas">edit source</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<p>The installation process in a production environment normally involves different roles in your organization. For example, physical or virtual machines for production use are normally managed by IT administrators, and the person who is going to install the suite therefore needs to request machines from an IT administrator, who will help prepare the requested machines. Typical roles that may be involved include:
</p>
<ul><li><b>Suite Admin</b>: the person who is going to install the suite. This person must have a good understanding of the entire installation process, request support from other appropriate personas as needed, and complete the installation once the environment is ready for installation. For this reason, installation tasks for Suite Admin are divided into two phases (phase 1 and phase 2).</li>
<li><b>IT Admin</b></li>
<li><b>Network Admin</b></li>
<li><b>Storage Admin</b></li>
<li><b>DB Admin</b></li>
<li><b>Server Admin</b></li>
<li><b>Directory Services Admin</b></li>
<li><b>Middleware</b></li>
<li><b>Security</b></li></ul>

